				<td colspan="2"><span>I finally got the hammer using charm but it took alot of tries as he resist alot and during the day will almost always aggro dragoons and sometimes the Cliff Gollem if your timing isn't right.
<br />

<br />
I finally did it at night when all the dragoons were out on &quot;patrol&quot; and pulled him out of the outpost alone using OOC then charmed him with the jade hanging on my cursor it was fast and easy to turn it in and get the hammer.
<br />

<br />
It is not a reliable means of &quot;escape&quot; if you get into trouble as it's a pain in the a$$ to get equipped fast enough and has a very slow delay ... waiting for it to proc while you're getting beat on with low hps is not a good situation.
<br />

<br />
IMO the best means of escape (if you want a gate type option) are potions of some sort, thou the casting time on them and chance of interupt is also a factor.   
<br />

<br />
The only reason I wanted the hammer was so I'd have a way out of Raids if no porters or translocaters were available and I didn't want to waste a Thurgadin Gate potion. (/duel someone on the raid to get it to proc).
<br />

<br />

